~ start
I made my first metroidvania platformer game in 2023, a month or two before I went back to university.
It was also a game in Godot and an entry to Metroidvania Month, though with a different character, story, and vibe, and overall just less development experience from me.
I’ve made and released a few shoot-em-up games before then, but that platformer was my first time indulging in a new genre I’ve always been curious about.
I was really proud of it, and got some valuable feedback from the Metroidvania Month community.
